A university student who went on the rampage with a knife on a busy underground train killing four people and injuring more than 20 others has been sentenced to death.

The New Taipei District Court in Taiwan sentenced 21-year-old Cheng Chieh 24 death sentences, one for each of his victims, for the rush-hour attack on a commuter train in the capital Taipei in May last year.

The ruling also deprived Cheng of his civil rights for the rest of his life.

