Appearing in court, Cheng showed no reaction when his sentences were announced.

Family members of the deceased who were present in court also welcomed the verdict, saying that giving Cheng the death penalty met public expectations.

Cheng's father Feng agreed, saying: 'Although he is our child, the crime he committed is unforgivable.

'He should be sentenced to death and face it himself. Only by so doing may the pains inflicted on the victims and the wounded and their families be slightly eased.

